<Base title="About & editorial standards" description="Who runs MindfulRoots, how we research supplements, and the editorial standards behind every profile.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">About</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-moss-deep">Why MindfulRoots exists</h1>
    <div class="prose-mr mt-6">
      <p>MindfulRoots started from a simple frustration: most pages selling mood supplements either over-promise wildly or bury the cautions that actually matter. We wanted a place that treats readers like adults — clear about what the research shows, honest about what it doesn't, and never pretending a capsule can replace real care.</p>

      <h2>Our editorial standards</h2>
      <p>Every supplement profile follows the same rules:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Evidence rating.</strong> Each supplement gets an honest tier — emerging, moderate, or well-studied — based on the quality and consistency of human trials, not marketing.</li>
        <li><strong>Cautions up front.</strong> Interactions and risks are stated plainly, never hidden at the bottom. Where a supplement needs real care (like 5-HTP with antidepressants), we say so loudly.</li>
        <li><strong>Support framing, not treatment claims.</strong> We describe supplements as mood, stress and sleep <em>support</em>. We never frame them as a treatment or cure for depression or any medical condition.</li>
        <li><strong>Care-forward.</strong> Every page points back toward professional and, where needed, crisis support.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>
      <p>MindfulRoots is reader-supported through affiliate links to iHerb. If you buy through one of our links, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. That funding model never changes our evidence ratings or which cautions we include — see our <a href="/disclosure/">full affiliate disclosure</a>.</p>

      <h2>What we are not</h2>
      <p>We are not doctors, and nothing here is medical advice. Supplements are a small, optional supporting piece of wellbeing — the foundations (sleep, movement, daylight, food, connection, and professional care when you need it) matter far more. If you are struggling, please see our <a href="/get-help/">Get help</a> page.</p>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft"><em>This is a placeholder About page for the MindfulRoots template. Replace this copy with real details about you or your team — including any relevant qualifications, which strengthen trust and SEO (E-E-A-T) in this space.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
